data.text:
Welcome to

Windsor Great Park

Part of the Windsor Estate, Windsor Great Park is an ancient Royal landscape of forests, grasslands, lakes and gardens. Visit and you will discover 1,000 years of history including historical monuments, rare wildlife and National Collections of plants and Champion Trees.

An operational Estate with farms, vineyard, commercial forestry as well as residential and commercial lettings, the Windsor Estate covers approximately 6,400 hectares (15,800 acres) stretching for some 10 miles from Windsor Castle to Camberley and is home to a thriving business community.

The Windsor Estate

As one of the UK’s leading rural estates, much of which is a site of Special Scientific Interest (SSSI), the Windsor Estate is part of The Crown Estate and includes Home Park Private, Windsor Great Park, Sunninghill Park and Swinley Forest.

Find out more

Discover Windsor Great Park

Windsor Great Park is open all year round and is free to enter. We do charge for parking, entry to The Savill Garden, and tickets for Adventure Play with these charges contributing to the conservation and stewardship work across the Windsor Estate.

Explore and plan your visit to help you make the most of your day.

Adventure Play is a unique, hand-crafted children’s play area in the heart of Windsor Great Park.

Commissioned by George V, The Savill Garden is a 35-acre haven of gardens, woodland and seasonal displays.

Environmental Centre

The Windsor Great Park Environmental Centre runs natural activity programmes for children, young people and adults with the Wildlife Trust (BBOWT).

Great Park

This season’s

highlights

Windsor Great Park is home to an impressive collection of plants and flowers from around the world which offer astounding displays to admire throughout the year.

The Gardens

From the breathtaking magnolias in spring to the rich, vibrant stems of dogwoods in the winter, there is always something new to see throughout the seasons.

Events

Windsor Great Park hosts a variety of events throughout the year with something for everyone to enjoy.

Swinley

Forest

From thrilling adventures to educational hands-on science exhibitions, Swinley Forest offers a wide range of activities and learning experiences.

Past, present and future

Our story

Visit the Windsor Estate and you will be stepping in to Windsor Great Park’s history. William the Conqueror hunted here. Queen Victoria held court here. Generation upon generation have loved, cherished and protected this special place for future generations to enjoy.

The Estate

The Windsor Estate is designated Site of Special Scientific Interest, a Special Area of Conservation and a Special Protection Area for the Conservation of Wild Birds.

The future

The Windsor Estate may be 1,000 years old, but the world isn’t standing still. There are new challenges to address and new opportunities to lead the way.

Membership

With world-class gardens, stunning vistas and outstanding facilities you may want to visit Windsor Great Park more regularly. Park for free and more, when you become a Member.
